%% KubeRay Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/CodeFlare
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant Dashboard as Ray Head Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant HeadGCS as Ray Head GCS<br/>6379/TCP TCP
    participant Worker as Ray Worker Pod
    participant ServeSvc as Serve Service<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>Bearer Token / HTTPS
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (RayCluster)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Service<br/>(10001,6379,8265,8080,8000)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Service
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route/Ingress<br/>(if enableIngress: true)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Autoscaler RBAC<br/>(SA, Role, RoleBinding)
    Worker->>HeadGCS: Connect to cluster<br/>6379/TCP (no encryption)

    Note over User,Client: Flow 2: RayJob Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR<br/>Bearer Token / HTTPS
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (RayJob)
    Operator->>Dashboard: Submit job via REST API<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (no auth)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create submitter K8s Job<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Note right of Dashboard: Job executes on<br/>Ray cluster

    Note over User,Client: Flow 3: RayService Serve Deployment

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayService CR<br/>Bearer Token / HTTPS
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (RayService)
    Operator->>Dashboard: Deploy Serve applications<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (no auth)
    Operator->>Dashboard: Poll Serve status<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (no auth)
    Client->>ServeSvc: Inference request<br/>8000/TCP HTTP (no auth)
    ServeSvc-->>Client: Inference response
